OL,3,CHow do tsunami warning systems work?
OL,5,FThe strongest earthquake in a decade
OL,6,Fhit Russia's east coast on Wednesday
OL,7,Fmorning.
OL,9,FThe 8.8 magnitude quake prompted
OL,10,Ftsunami alerts across the Pacific, as
OL,11,Fwaves pushed forward towards Russia,
OL,12,FJapan, Hawaii and the United States'
OL,13,FWest Coast, as well as many other
OL,14,Fnations.
OL,16,FTsunamis can't be predicted. They
OL,17,Fdon't occur during a specific season,
OL,18,Fthey don't strike in the same place,
OL,19,Fand they don't follow any pattern that
OL,20,Fwould allow scientists to estimate how
OL,21,Fstrong the next one could be.
