OL,3,CHow do tsunami warning systems work?
OL,5,FJapan's functioned as a local warning
OL,6,Fsystem, while the USA's covered more
OL,7,Fdistance.
OL,9,FIn the aftermath of the 1960 Chilean
OL,10,Fearthquake and tsunami, which killed
OL,11,Fhundreds of people in total across
OL,12,FChile, Hawaii, Japan, and the
OL,13,FPhilippines, the nations of the
OL,14,FPacific decided to coordinate efforts.
OL,16,FMost earthquakes and tsunamis occur in
OL,17,Fthe Pacific Ocean, as it holds the
OL,18,Flargest ocean basin and the "Ring of
OL,19,FFire".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
