OL,3,CHow do tsunami warning systems work?
OL,5,FSeismic waves travel around 100 times
OL,6,Ffaster than tsunamis, meaning they can
OL,7,Fbe analysed far earlier than other
OL,8,Fmethods.
OL,10,FSeismic networks, a collection of
OL,11,Fstations whose job it is to measure
OL,12,Fground movement, can provide
OL,13,Finformation about an earthquake's
OL,14,Flocation, depth, and magnitude.
OL,16,FTsunami warning centres are then able
OL,17,Fto use this information to determine
OL,18,Fwhether a tsunami could have been
OL,19,Fformed, and whether it is necessary to
OL,20,Fissue a tsunami alert.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
